data.title: Where to fish
data.text:

Michigan has more than 11,000 inland lakes. For about 2,700 of these, we have inland lake maps available.

Michigan has more than 130 campgrounds that are less then one mile from a designated trout stream or lake.

Want to fish southeast Michigan's Great Lakes areas (St. Clair System and Lake Erie), Lake Huron, Lake Michigan or Lake Superior ... but you aren't sure when or where to go?

Our Great Lakes Fishing Roadmaps (found below) are starting points to provide you with information on many fishing sites and times of the year when great opportunities exist. Whether you're a seasoned angler or new to the sport these roadmaps can provide great insight into fishing these waters. Take a look (accessible versions also available below)!
